HEADWORD: Geat
<hw>Geat</hw> <pr>(g⟦emac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Gate</er>
a door.]</ety> <fld>(Founding)</fld> <def>The channel or spout through
which molten metal runs into a mold in casting.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>git</asp>, <asp>gate</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
